### Features ###
- Fully vectorise getTDS(). It currently only vectorises over postcodes when
  type is set to "full".
- Add the ability to search by output area to getTDS().
- Add the ability to specify partial prefixes and suffixes, and to be able to
  specify both at once in getTDS().
- Incorporate 2001 UK census data into the .dat_oa data frame, and add a "year"
  parameter to getTDS() to allow the specification of the Townsend data year.
- Make the error messages and warnings friendlier.

### Vignettes ###
- Complete the main package vignette.
- Use aggregated GP data in the vignette to simulate a UK population and produce
  a risk map that could be added to the vignette.
- Make a vignette that uses postcode data to produce a map of deprivation in
  inner London.

### Unit Tests ###
- Add tests to check that the input and output vector lengths match for the
  QDR*() functions.
